    • Field Detail

      • stackData

        private java.util.ArrayList<E> stackData
        Inner data of stack. It's ArrayList because of strange Java's error - you can't do this in classes: 
        
 E[] stackData = new E[];
        Where E is generic type.

      • pop

        public E pop()
        Implements method from superclass. This method is synchronized because JavaFX creates many threads, and I don't need exceptions caused by stacks.

        Note: if stack is empty - returns null, not exception.

        Specified by:
        pop in interface LIFOQueue<E>
        Returns:
        last removed object.

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Clears all items of queue. Used to make code 
        
 for ( ; stack.length() > 0; stack.pop());
        more compact. Now, it will be 
        
 stack.clear();
        Specified by:
        clear in interface LIFOQueue<E>
